This paper proposes a novel approach for semi-supervised learning using powers of the Laplacian matrix. The paper focuses on improving classification performance in cases of fuzzy graphs or unbalanced labeled data. This topic is closely related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
